to the All-Russian Scientific Research
Institute of Experimental Physics

296
00:31:07,464 --> 00:31:11,560
and is the birthplace
of our first atomic bomb.

297
00:31:12,169 --> 00:31:16,970
Many of our greatest scientists
worked here and many still do.

298
00:31:17,174 --> 00:31:18,971
Since 1 995,

299
00:31:19,176 --> 00:31:22,839
we have dismantled
over 1 0,000 nuclear devices.

300
00:31:27,718 --> 00:31:31,620
We tried so hard to get in here
over the years.

301
00:31:31,822 --> 00:31:34,290
I sent three people.

302
00:31:35,626 --> 00:31:38,117
They all died trying.

303
00:32:04,688 --> 00:32:07,213
What does the T-shirt say?

304
00:32:07,424 --> 00:32:13,021
"I am a bomb technician. If you
see me running... try to catch up."

305
00:32:16,934 --> 00:32:18,231
OK.

306
00:32:19,370 --> 00:32:23,864
Sir, I'm sorry. Just one quick thing.
I'm sure it's nothing.

307
00:32:24,074 --> 00:32:28,636
According to this, there are
1 7 senior scientists on duty today.

308
00:32:31,081 --> 00:32:32,514
I only count 1 4.

309
00:32:33,884 --> 00:32:40,255
Doctors Milinov, Orlov and Spassky.
They don't seem to be here.

310
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,727
I will make inquiries.

311
00:32:43,927 --> 00:32:47,055
Dr Milinov is out sick.
Orlov is on vacation.

312
00:32:47,264 --> 00:32:50,825
Spassky, I'm grieved to say,
was killed

313
00:32:51,035 --> 00:32:54,061
driving his car to work
just this past week.

314
00:32:59,143 --> 00:33:01,509
We move on, shall we?

315
00:33:02,179 --> 00:33:03,476
Please.

316
00:33:06,183 --> 00:33:10,882
Very impressive. You almost seem
to have that information memorized.

317
00:33:11,088 --> 00:33:13,886
