370
00:38:41,251 --> 00:38:44,982
- Let's talk response.
- The worst thing we can do is nothing.

371
00:38:45,188 --> 00:38:49,887
If he gets away with chemical weapons,
what's next? Biological, nuclear?

372
00:38:50,093 --> 00:38:54,792
OK. Short of gassing the Kremlin,
what's the strongest response?

373
00:38:54,998 --> 00:38:57,694
- We send in peacekeepers.
- Chechnya's not sovereign.

374
00:38:57,901 --> 00:39:02,929
They requested recognition, so we
give it. Not full diplomatic, provisional.

375
00:39:03,140 --> 00:39:07,907
Then the Chechens request assistance
and we send in peacekeepers.

376
00:39:08,111 --> 00:39:11,569
- How do you get them in there?
- We fly them in from Turkey.

377
00:39:11,782 --> 00:39:16,549
- Over Armenian air space?
- To screw Russia? They won't complain.

378
00:39:18,188 --> 00:39:21,521
Let's do it. Nemerov can choke on it.

379
00:39:22,459 --> 00:39:23,790
Bill?

380
00:39:24,694 --> 00:39:26,628
- Dr Ryan.
- Yes, sir.

381
00:39:26,830 --> 00:39:28,855
What do you think?

382
00:39:34,538 --> 00:39:37,371
Conventional wisdom suggests

383
00:39:37,574 --> 00:39:40,475
that Nemerov is playing
the traditional Russian role:

384
00:39:40,677 --> 00:39:44,636
be aggressive, flex your muscles,
dare the world to stop you.

385
00:39:44,848 --> 00:39:48,340
- But Nemerov isn't conventional.
- He acts like a hardliner.

386
00:39:48,552 --> 00:39:50,952
With respect, I don't think he is one.

387
00:39:51,154 --> 00:39:55,614
He just gassed the capital of another
country. With respect, you're wrong.

388
00:39:55,826 --> 00:40:00,991
- So what are we wasting our time for?
- What if he didn't order the attack?

389
00:40:02,933 --> 00:40:06,232
What if Nemerov
didn't order the attack?

390
00:40:07,237 --> 00:40:11,765
What if it was a... a rogue general?

391
00:40:11,975 --> 00:40:16,071
Or a military unit frustrated they
couldn't get the rebels out of the city?

392
00:40:16,279 --> 00:40:21,410
Have you reason to believe he didn't
order it, or are you just floating this?

393
00:40:23,086 --> 00:40:24,576
You don't know.

394
00:40:28,892 --> 00:40:33,454
I don't think he did it, sir.
I would bet he didn't do it.

395
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:40,366
Will senior staff remain behind
for a few minutes, please?

396
00:41:02,959 --> 00:41:06,588
Russia's newly-installed president,
Alexander Nemerov,

397
00:41:06,796 --> 00:41:12,234
has just begun to address the state.
We join him in progress.

398
00:41:16,406 --> 00:41:20,001
For ten years now,
we have contended...

399
00:41:20,210 --> 00:41:23,236
Excuse me. Could you turn that up?

400
00:41:24,347 --> 00:41:26,611
...toward innocent Russian citizens.

401
00:41:28,652 --> 00:41:30,051
Finally...

402
00:41:31,188 --> 00:41:34,749
...every nation has a right
to defend itself.

403
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:39,356
This terrorism must end.

404
00:41:40,397 --> 00:41:44,697
The bombing of Chechnya...
was my decision.

405
00:41:48,572 --> 00:41:50,597
Nice going, ace.

406
00:42:02,752 --> 00:42:04,117
Who did it?

407
00:42:04,321 --> 00:42:07,722
General Pildysh, General Mitkin.
Unhappy old Communists.

408
00:42:07,924 --> 00:42:09,755
Bastards.

409
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:13,020
- Relieve them of command.
- I will shoot them myself.

410
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:15,460
Just disappear them.

411
00:42:15,665 --> 00:42:19,965
Their execution would tell the world
I didn't have control.

412
00:42:20,170 --> 00:42:25,369
These days, better to appear guilty
than impotent.

413
00:42:28,511 --> 00:42:31,344
How is our Russian friend
affected by this?

414
00:42:34,117 --> 00:42:39,987
I am not affected.
I remain devoted to our little plan.

415
00:42:40,991 --> 00:42:44,392
At what you're charging us,
I am not surprised.

416
00:42:44,594 --> 00:42:48,052
- And the American?
- Mr Mason is a believer.

417
00:42:48,265 --> 00:42:51,996
I put a little extra
in the escrow account for him.

418
00:42:52,202 --> 00:42:56,639
- Why?
